  "response_text": "A polished wooden table in an IHOP dining room is covered edge to edge with plated food. In the background, softly out of focus, a person in a magenta top stands or moves near a booth. Across the table are several white plates: burgers with fries, fried chicken pieces, stacks of pancakes, breakfast items with eggs and bacon, golden fried appetizers with dipping sauce, and a sweet dish topped with whipped cream and chocolate chips. The restaurant setting feels warm and casual, with the food brightly lit against a darker, blurred dining area.\n\nThe view moves in closer to the breakfast and dessert items. In the foreground, a plate holds two sunny-side-up eggs, strips of bacon, and a browned rectangular breakfast item. To the left are fries and a bowl of fried appetizers. Behind them sits a dessert plate with rolled pancakes or crepes filled with a cream-like filling, topped with a tall swirl of whipped cream and scattered chocolate chips. Large white text begins appearing over the food, building into “$5 at IHOP,” with the IHOP wordmark and its red smile underneath.\n\nThe food arrangement changes to another close display. A stack of pancakes with butter and syrup sits near the center-left, with crispy fried chicken beside it. A burger with cheese, lettuce, tomato, red onion, and fries fills the right side. In the background are another burger, hash browns, and fried appetizers with a small cup of red dipping sauce. The white “$5 at IHOP” text remains centered over the plates, and smaller white text underneath reads “$6 in some locations.” The plates are arranged like a menu spread, emphasizing variety: pancakes, burgers, fries, chicken, hash browns, and appetizers all visible at once.\n\nA close-up focuses on a short stack of pancakes on a white plate. Syrup drips down the sides, a scoop of butter sits on top, and a fork enters from the upper left, pressing into a cut piece of pancake. Fried chicken is visible to the right of the stack, and a white IHOP cup is blurred in the background.\n\nThe scene then shows a man seated at a restaurant counter or table. He appears middle-aged, with light-to-medium skin, dark slicked-back hair, and a thick dark mustache. He wears a light blue dress shirt, dark vest, tie, an ID badge on a lanyard, and a round patch on his vest, giving him a staff or manager-like appearance. In front of him are several plates: a burger and fries to his left, a glass of Pepsi, fried appetizers and pancakes in the center, and an IHOP coffee mug to his right. A large blue IHOP sign is blurred behind him, with other diners seated in the background. He holds a fork with a bite of food near his mouth, then lowers it and looks toward the burger and fries, chewing with a serious, satisfied concentration before leaning forward toward the plates.\n\nThe commercial ends on a final menu-style layout. The table of food returns, with many plates spread across the foreground. At the top left, a dark sign glows with blue neon-style text reading “IHOPPY HOUR.” On the right, large white text reads “$5 Menu,” with smaller text below: “$6 in some locations.” Near the lower left, white text says “2 - 10pm Everyday.” Along the bottom center, bold white text reads “Free Delivery on IHOP.com,” followed by smaller fine print about delivery availability and hours. The background remains an IHOP dining room with a blurred person in magenta on the right, while the food and promotional text stay sharp and prominent.",
